{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>This week was the culmination of all the research and design strategy I'd been\nspearheading over the last month.</p>\n<p>My goal was to simplify the current workflow of discovering events the target\naudience might be interested in, based on relevancy, location, and those around\nthem. In an effort to illustrate the groundwork of design language and pattern\nlibrary research, information architecture and content strategy, cognitive and\nsocial psychology, and universal design and accessibility, I've produced a\nprototype that incorporates a number of these considerations.</p>\n<p>Due to time constraints and resources, I only managed to perform usability\ntesting with one participant, the details of which can be found at the end of\nthis article.</p>\n<p>As a learning challenge for myself, I decided to use some tools that I wasn't\ntoo familiar with, Adobe Experience Design and Illustrator, in an effort to try\nthem out and determine whether I'd use them on other projects in future.</p>\n<h2 id=\"proposed-user-flow\"><a href=\"#proposed-user-flow\" aria-label=\"proposed user flow permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Proposed user flow</h2>\n<p>My first task was to develop a user flow that I felt was suitable for my primary\npersona, <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNNlhldnFENlJOUmc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Eoin</a>,\nand the\n<a href=\"../gaining-empathy#experience-mapping-and-storyboarding\">experience mapping and storyboarding</a>\nexercises I conducted in my previous article on gaining empathy.</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5231c5283a9c2ff64ddae06e866be28c/8fdf3/User-flow.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 504px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"User flow\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5231c5283a9c2ff64ddae06e866be28c/8fdf3/User-flow.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5231c5283a9c2ff64ddae06e866be28c/aca85/User-flow.jpg 163w,\n/static/5231c5283a9c2ff64ddae06e866be28c/0954f/User-flow.jpg 325w,\n/static/5231c5283a9c2ff64ddae06e866be28c/8fdf3/User-flow.jpg 504w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 504px) 100vw, 504px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>User flow</figcaption>\n<p>The final user flow is as follows:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upon opening the application, Eoin's able to see recommendations based on his\nfriends, location, and musical interests</li>\n<li>To discover what's happening this weekend, he opens the filters and selects\nthe correct dates</li>\n<li>Once the filtered results roll in, he selects an event that interests him</li>\n<li>He's able to view information about this event, and scrolls down</li>\n<li>He sees which artists are supporting and which of his friends are attending</li>\n<li>Finally, he's able to compare the price of tickets and navigate to the vendor\nof his choosing</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Once decided on the basic flow, I took the opportunity to develop a general\naesthetic guideline for the outputted designs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"design-languages-and-pattern-libraries\"><a href=\"#design-languages-and-pattern-libraries\" aria-label=\"design languages and pattern libraries permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Design Languages and Pattern Libraries</h2>\n<p>As I made the decision early on to develop the prototype to be used on a\nsmartphone, I inevitably ended up conforming to Google's <a href=\"%5Bhttps://www.google.com/design/spec/material-design/introduction%5D\">material design</a> guidelines in places, incorporating appropriate interface elements where\nnecessary to ensure the application felt right.</p>\n<p>However, as discussed in my article on\n<a href=\"../design-languages-pattern-libraries#yelp-styleguide\">design languages and pattern libraries</a>,\nI also wanted to apply bright, clear, and engaging aesthetics to the designs\nwithout distracting the audience from their current task.</p>\n<p>I developed a very minimal colour palette, similar in simplicity to that of\nYelp's, that was specific and fit-for-purpose across the application:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Primary colour:</strong> #4178be - Used for primary actions such as navigation</li>\n<li><strong>Primary colour:</strong> #e71d32 - Dominant background colour</li>\n<li><strong>Secondary colour:</strong> #4b8400 - Reserved for special actions like discovering\nprices</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f379d2520ba6b868f8d9a05f7c067edb/8594d/Colour-palette.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 316px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 31.645569620253163%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAGCAYAAADDl76dAAAACXBIWXMAAAsSAAALEgHS3X78AAAAT0lEQVQY02NwrN33Hwn/c6rZ88+q6dj/pvD29o/imu9fyJn8fy5r9A+EX8gZ/X8vbvK+J0Kk0qWD4b9PM8N/72aGf94tQBqKGUYNHHwGAgDB/P0JObf/ZwAAAABJRU5ErkJggg=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Colour palette\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/f379d2520ba6b868f8d9a05f7c067edb/8594d/Colour-palette.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f379d2520ba6b868f8d9a05f7c067edb/19bd1/Colour-palette.png 163w,\n/static/f379d2520ba6b868f8d9a05f7c067edb/8594d/Colour-palette.png 316w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 316px) 100vw, 316px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Colour palette</figcaption>\n<p>The filter button present on the landing view shows how I adapted the\n<a href=\"https://www.google.com/design/spec/components/buttons-floating-action-button.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Floating Action Button</a>\nof material design to fall in line with the colour palette I adopted:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6d66a706eee62589b5d538f42a13d2c0/36d18/Filter.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 101px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Filter\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6d66a706eee62589b5d538f42a13d2c0/36d18/Filter.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6d66a706eee62589b5d538f42a13d2c0/36d18/Filter.png 101w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 101px) 100vw, 101px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Filter</figcaption>\n<p>In order to maintain it's own style as an application regardless of what\nplatform it may be on, I made a decision to opt-out of using Roboto as a\ntypeface, and instead use the classic Helvetica with a number of different\nweights.</p>\n<p>Now I'll look at how the information architecture and content strategy developed\nearlier on fits in with my proposed solution.</p>\n<h2 id=\"information-architecture-and-content-strategy\"><a href=\"#information-architecture-and-content-strategy\" aria-label=\"information architecture and content strategy permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Information Architecture and Content Strategy</h2>\n<p>I produced a number of design artifacts while auditing\n<a href=\"http://www.tickets.ie\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Tickets.ie</a> with regards to information architecture and\ncontent strategy.</p>\n<p>Although I never fully realised high-fidelity interfaces for individual artists\nand venues, the links between these sections remain for efficient navigation.\nThe metadata described in the proposed\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=1RkLuzMdiFI6pFTV3tAWfy5JzLK2fJIKnDQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">content model and entity relationship diagram</a>\nrings true across my final design.</p>\n<p>Looking back at my\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=1CeML0_uEil-w-kM94HQg14zjiE_zuyzQ9Tv-YYDUjRU\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">core sample content audit</a>,\nI also addressed the following red flags from the current website:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>High character counts on navigation links and subheadings</li>\n<li>Removed any redundant headings and labels, making the content it conveyed more\napparent</li>\n<li>Produced consistent tone, voice, and wording across calls-to-action and labels</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Moving on from this, I'll discuss how I incorporated cognitive and social\npsychological aspects into my designs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"cognitive-and-social-psychology\"><a href=\"#cognitive-and-social-psychology\" aria-label=\"cognitive and social psychology permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Cognitive and Social Psychology</h2>\n<p>In my article on\n<a href=\"../cognitive-social-psychology#cognitive-psychology\">cognitive and social psychology</a>,\nI spoke about reducing cognitive load by making information easier to digest\nusing a combination of media and text - here's an example of that in the design\nsolution:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a4365407130edb39c1fc4fdf20964af2/44727/Reducing-cognitive-load.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 450px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 64.8888888888889%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Reducing cognitive load\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a4365407130edb39c1fc4fdf20964af2/44727/Reducing-cognitive-load.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a4365407130edb39c1fc4fdf20964af2/19bd1/Reducing-cognitive-load.png 163w,\n/static/a4365407130edb39c1fc4fdf20964af2/d3bcb/Reducing-cognitive-load.png 325w,\n/static/a4365407130edb39c1fc4fdf20964af2/44727/Reducing-cognitive-load.png 450w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Reducing cognitive load</figcaption>\n<p>Above we can also see linking to the venue that the event is being held in,\nappealing to people's want to cut corners in common workflows.</p>\n<p>We also see the social psychological concept of scarcity taking effect - showing\nhow many tickets are remaining may persuade the target audience to act quickly\nand purchase a ticket themselves!</p>\n<p>Seeing just how many people you know are attending the event may sway you to\nattend yourself, so the concept of social proof comes into play at the bottom of\nany events details page:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/eed3c91ed5dd638f26de96df471761e2/135ae/Social-proof-contrast.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 300px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 180.66666666666663%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Social proof and contrast load\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/eed3c91ed5dd638f26de96df471761e2/135ae/Social-proof-contrast.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/eed3c91ed5dd638f26de96df471761e2/19bd1/Social-proof-contrast.png 163w,\n/static/eed3c91ed5dd638f26de96df471761e2/135ae/Social-proof-contrast.png 300w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Social proof and contrast</figcaption>\n<p>The use of contrast in both colour and size for the event tracking and buying\nbuttons makes the buying call-to-action more attractive.</p>\n<p>Lastly I'll touch on universal (inclusive) design and accessibility, and how I\ntook the research I did in this area into my final designs.</p>\n<h2 id=\"universal-design-and-accessibility\"><a href=\"#universal-design-and-accessibility\" aria-label=\"universal design and accessibility permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Universal design and accessibility</h2>\n<p>As discussed in my\n<a href=\"../universal-inclusive-design-accessibility#equitable-use\">post on this topic</a>,\nI've made considerations for a number of principles of universal design:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Equitable use</li>\n<li>Flexibility in use</li>\n<li>Simple and intuitive use</li>\n<li>Size and space for approach and use</li>\n</ul>\n<p>To validate my proposed solution for equitable use, I tested my designs against\ndifferent levels of colour blindness. One of the most challenging was\ntritanopia, an extremely rare condition that renders blue and green almost\nindistinguishable. The colour palette I developed above provides what I feel is\nenough of a noticeable distinction between actions:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2d1e4140fca160d268810738b829ded2/eac10/Tritanopia-comparison.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 332px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 123.49397590361444%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Tritanopia comparison\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/2d1e4140fca160d268810738b829ded2/eac10/Tritanopia-comparison.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2d1e4140fca160d268810738b829ded2/19bd1/Tritanopia-comparison.png 163w,\n/static/2d1e4140fca160d268810738b829ded2/d3bcb/Tritanopia-comparison.png 325w,\n/static/2d1e4140fca160d268810738b829ded2/eac10/Tritanopia-comparison.png 332w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 332px) 100vw, 332px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Tritanopia comparison</figcaption>\n<p>To demonstrate flexibility in use, I produced filtering controls that would\nprovide the target audience choice in the methods that they used for discovering\nupcoming events, which they could do at their own pace:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a23e6bf9bf4b153cf5949698ae8affe9/86068/Filter-panel.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 321px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 79.75077881619937%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Filter panel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/a23e6bf9bf4b153cf5949698ae8affe9/86068/Filter-panel.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a23e6bf9bf4b153cf5949698ae8affe9/19bd1/Filter-panel.png 163w,\n/static/a23e6bf9bf4b153cf5949698ae8affe9/86068/Filter-panel.png 321w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 321px) 100vw, 321px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Filter panel</figcaption>\n<p>With regards to simple and intuitive use, the filters above illustrate the\nflexibility of manipulating the event listings depending on the options they\nselect. There are also multiple avenues of navigation between artist, event, and\nvenue:</p>\n<p><a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/16140d51b396e2845483df21d2e2d870/01387/Navigation.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 320px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 129.99999999999997%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Navigation\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/16140d51b396e2845483df21d2e2d870/01387/Navigation.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/16140d51b396e2845483df21d2e2d870/19bd1/Navigation.png 163w,\n/static/16140d51b396e2845483df21d2e2d870/01387/Navigation.png 320w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 320px) 100vw, 320px\"\n      />\n  </span>\n  </a></p>\n<figcaption>Navigation</figcaption>\n<p>Finally, for size and space for approach and use I looked at adding key actions\nlike filtering closer to the user's hand. As well as this, consideration was\nmade for the user's comfort, with no touch target being shorter than 40 pixels\nin width or height.</p>\n<p>With the prototype finished, it's now time to see it in action - Here's a\n<a href=\"http://adobe.ly/1VAFHbh\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">link</a> to the high-fidelity solution I produced!</p>\n<h2 id=\"usability-testing\"><a href=\"#usability-testing\" aria-label=\"usability testing permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Usability testing</h2>\n<p>As much research and design effort that's put in throughout the course of a\nproject, you never really know which way it's going to go until you've placed\nyour designs in front of a user to validate, in order to identify problems with\nthe target audience's interaction with a product.</p>\n<p>The goal of the testing was to determine whether the design approach used as a\nresult of all the considerations I made throughout the project made sense, or in\nKrug's words, \"Get it\" testing (2006). Specifically:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A user will understand how to find information on events they care about</li>\n<li>A user will be able to discover events to attend at any given time period</li>\n<li>A user will be able to determine their best option for purchasing a ticket</li>\n</ul>\n<p>In order to streamline the testing, a\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNUFY2a2Q4OFJnSFk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">consent form</a>,\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNS2QzalN0Nm0tQ0U\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">facilitation script</a>,\nand <a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNanBVa0V2OGVKVmM\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">test plan</a>\nwere created.</p>\n<p>Testing of the prototype was performed on a Google Nexus 5X in Google Chrome\nusing the shareable link that Adobe Experience Design generated, with screen,\nface, and voice being recorded using <a href=\"https://lookback.io/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Lookback</a>.</p>\n<p>With limited time to wrap things up, unfortunately I only managed to perform one\n<a href=\"https://lookback.io/watch/tY9Ra3rgGoKfStW3A\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">usability test</a> on the finished\nprototype.</p>\n<p>The participant was delegated three tasks to attempt while thinking aloud over\nthe space of 10 minutes:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Find out when Bell X1 are playing next</li>\n<li>Find out what events are happing this weekend</li>\n<li>Discover the best ticket prices for Battles</li>\n</ol>\n<p>The participant came across a number of issues within the application:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>There was issues with the lack of scrolling functionality within Adobe\nExperience Design - the participant would inadvertently refresh the web\nbrowser when attempting to scroll, having to restart</li>\n<li>The participant selected 'Upcoming' to see what events were on this weekend</li>\n<li>The Floating Action Button was an unfamiliar concept to the participant</li>\n<li>The icon for the filter reset confused the participant</li>\n<li>It was not apparent to the participant that the button for confirming filters\nwas a button</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If I were to produce another iteration of the prototype, there are a number of\nconsiderations I would have to make based on the problems identified above.</p>\n<p>In order to prevent confusion between the two in future, it's worth considering\na change of copy from 'Upcoming' to 'My Events' or something along those lines.</p>\n<p>Although not a frequent Android user, it may be worth moving the functionality\nof the Floating Action Button somewhere else on the screen (perhaps in the\nheader beside the search) in order for the design to be platform-agnostic.</p>\n<p>There was also confusion around the filter panel - it could be a case of moving\nthe confirm button to the right-hand side to make it more obvious that it's a\nbutton or distancing it a bit from the label. The reset button icon also needs\nto be revised, or perhaps it should be spelt out in English rather than relying\non iconography.</p>\n<h2 id=\"conclusion\"><a href=\"#conclusion\" aria-label=\"conclusion permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>Throughout the course of the last few months, as well as tightening up some\nvisual design and prototype development skills, I gained some new knowledge in\nareas I had yet to touch on, including:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Information architecture and content strategy</li>\n<li>Cognitive and social psychology</li>\n<li>Universal design</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now that I've been exposed to these concepts and ideas, I'll be able to bring\nthem forward into my designs naturally in the future.</p>\n<p>There was a lot of things that slowed me down by own doing - I wanted to\nchallenge myself using tools I had little familiarity with, and as a result the\nlearning curve was steep and the prototype wasn't as fully developed as I\nwould've like it to have been.</p>\n<p>However, I think the act of researching design languages and pattern libraries,\nuniversal design, and producing mock-ups at a high-fidelity has given me a\nbetter eye for visual elements like colour, layout, and typography.</p>\n<p>To wrap up, I'll leave with my <a href=\"https://youtu.be/ukCEd6OgGpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">screencast</a>, which\nhas consolidated the entire process from start to finish.</p>\n<h2 id=\"resources\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.google.com/design/spec/material-design/introduction.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Google material design</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://adobe.ly/1VAFHbh\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">High-fidelity solution</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://youtu.be/ukCEd6OgGpg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Screencast</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNWWdnS010NXNhUWc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Screencast uploads</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNZlVsbGd2akh5M1U\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Prototype uploads</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://lookback.io/watch/tY9Ra3rgGoKfStW3A\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Usability test</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=1FfljBzfQCazBGK0SXLC3GUzNUsXIMgyWoQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">User flow</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/open?id=0BzA9UyHASmcNc2xsUl81b01ZbWc\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Usability testing uploads</a></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"date":"17 April, 2016","title":"High-fidelity solution"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2016/universal-inclusive-design-accessibility/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Universal (inclusive) design and accessibility"}},"next":null,"slug":"/2016/high-fidelity-solution/"}}